==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[#French|bandeau]], from Old French [[bandel]], diminutive of [[bande]] ‘band’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈbændəʊ/}} ''(or as French, below)'' (''UK'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun|bandeaux}}

# A [[band]] for the [[hair]].
#:''She wore a '''bandeau''' in her hair.''
# A [[brassiere]], especially when narrow or strapless; a top made from a narrow band of fabric.

